FBIS4-743 "drafr073_d_94014" FBIS-AFR-94-073 Daily Report 15 Apr 1994 SOUTHERN AFRICA Mozambique Renamo Appoints Dhlakama for Presidential Election Renamo Appoints Dhlakama for Presidential Election MB1504091694 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network in Portuguese 0900 GMT 15 Apr 94 MB1504091694 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network Portuguese BFN [Text] Channel Africa reported this morning that the Mozambique National Resistance [Renamo] has elected Afonso Dhlakama, its leader, as Renamo candidate in the presidential elections scheduled for October. Quoting the Renamo secretary general, Channel Africa reported that the decision was made at the minicongress being held at the Renamo headquarters in Maringue. The source said that Dhlakama's candidacy was unanimously approved by all attending the meeting. Renamo's congress, which was scheduled to wind up today, is now focusing on issues relating to electoral strategy and it could last longer than initially expected.
